	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName> <date>July 26. 1865</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">It may possibly be known to you<lb/> that a controversy has arisen in the Christian Church<lb/> regarding the use in public worship of hymns of<lb/> praise&#44; which are not found in the canon of<lb/> Sacred Scripture.  The example of the ancient Jew&#45;<lb/>ish &#8220;church&#8221; has been claimed as a precedent a&#61;<lb/>gainst their use.  As this controversy has arisen in<lb/> days when Talmudic and cognate studies are less<lb/> zealously pursued among Christian Scholars&#44; than<lb/> in the days of <persName>Lightfoot</persName> and <persName>Gill</persName>&#44; the subject is<lb/> one which we must refer to those whose peculiar<lb/> studies fit them to solve the difficulty.  Your wide<lb/> and eminent reputation as a scholar has led<lb/> us to trouble you with the following inquiries<lb/> your kind attention to which will much oblige<lb/> a large number of your fellow citizens.</p>
				<p>I&#8212;Were there any other hymns of praise than<lb/> the psalms of <persName>David</persName>&#44; sued in the ancient&#45;<lb/>temple or synagogue service of the Jewish<lb/> &#8220;church&#8221; prior to the final destruction of</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>the <placeName>Holy City</placeName> by <persName>Titus</persName>&#63;</p>
				<p>II&#8212;If so&#44; were these other hymns of praise<lb/> taken exclusively from the canonical scrip&#45;<lb/>tures or not&#63;</p>
				<p>III&#8212;Does the three&#45;fold distinction laid down<lb/> by <persName>Paul</persName> in his Epistle to Colossians II. 16.<lb/> and to the Ephesians V.19. refer to any recog&#45;<lb/>nized division or arrangement of the Book<lb/> of Psalms&#44; or is it a general description of the<lb/> species of sacred poetry in current use at that<lb/> time&#63;</p>
				<p>IV. If there were in use hymns of praise<lb/> not to be found in the canonical scriptures<lb/> are they still extant&#44; and can you refer us to<lb/> any work easily obtained which contains<lb/> either them&#44; or any information on the<lb/> subject.</p>
				<p>V. Was the entire Book of Psalms used in<lb/> the ancient temple or synagogue service<lb/> and if not&#44; what part <hi rend="underline">was</hi> used&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We are very sorry to trouble you<lb/> with such a long list of queries&#44; but<lb/> hope that you will have it in your power<lb/> to give us an answer at an early</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>day&#44; without putting yourself to any in&#45;<lb/>convenience</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours very Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">George S. Chambers</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">R. E. Thompson</persName></p>
				<p>Address us&#8212;<placeName><hi rend="underline">Box 901</hi>&#8212;<hi rend="underline">Philada. Post Office</hi></placeName></p>
		</body>
